      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be performed on geometry, fluid properties, and operating conditions that are representative of the intended clinical use environment.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry rather than a specific commercial VAD design; blood analog fluid was used in place of whole blood, reducing physiological fidelity substantially."
